<br>
I'm not throwing in the towel on EQ by any means.  I still find it an enjoyable game, but for roleplayers I'm thinking DAoC is going to be offering a better environment.<br>
<br>
The game is being *released* with a Roleplay Designated Server called Percival where In Character communcations will be *enforced* in public channels.  I'll post the actual rules set here:<br>
<br>
( This info taken from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotvault.com">www.camelotvault.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> )<br>
<br>
Everyone at Mythic Entertainment realizes what an exciting and important thing we are doing, as we open our first Roleplaying server. It is important for us to provide the people who really want to Rolepay, with an environment that they can do this in. Therefore, we have come up with several enhancements to our standard Code of Conduct and Disciplinary Policy. These enhancements are intended to make the environments on DAoC roleplaying servers as fun as possible for the people involved, and to dissuade people from coming to the server who are not roleplayers, or people who come to interfere with the roleplaying of others. <br>
One of the main things that will change is our approach to enforcement of the Code of Conduct and Naming Policy. We will be much stricter on our interpretation of these policies and will enforce them with a much heavier hand. The message is &quot;Do not come to this server if you do not want to Roleplay&quot;. We are very committed to giving excellent customer service on this and all of our game servers, and will do what we can to make playing on the roleplaying servers a great experience for all DAoC roleplayers. <br>
The three main additions to our Policies are outlined below: <br>
<br>
Naming Policy for Rolepaying Servers. <br>
1. All names must fit into the medieval setting. <br>
2. All names must fit into the realm that you are playing in. <br>
All policy enforcement for names on the roleplaying servers will be done aggressively by members of the DAoC CS staff, of Server Lead and higher authority. It is in Mythic's sole judgment whether a name breaks the policy, and we will rename characters accordingly. If you see someone with a name that obviously breaks the roleplaying ruleset, please report them. <br>
<br>
Communication Policy for Roleplaying Server. <br>
1. All communication on the roleplay server must be appropriate for the medieval time-period (in-character). This means no talking about Soda-pop, Baseball, etc... <br>
2. If a guild, group or person agrees that out-of-character communication is acceptable, then Mythic will not interfere with this decision within /Guild, /Group, /Friend or /Sends communication. There is never a time when out-of-character communication is acceptable in /Broadcast, /Say, or /Shout. <br>
If someone is breaking the roleplaying communication policy on the server, you MUST ask them to stop before reporting them. If they stop when asked, and do not repeat their out-of-character communication, then the problem is solved and there is no need to contact customer support. If someone persists in breaking the roleplaying communication policy, then report them using the /Appeal command, and DAoC Customer Support will investigate. <br>
<br>
Event Interference <br>
1. Any interference or disruption of scheduled events, whether run by players or by Mythic Staff, is strictly prohibited. <br>
<br>
If you cannot abide by these rules, DO NOT play on these servers. Mythic Entertainment has a strict policy of enforcement regarding these rules, and will not tolerate players coming to this server who do not or will not roleplay. Breaking any of the above rules can result in actions against your account to include warnings, banishment from the roleplay servers, suspensions, and even termination of your account (based on the severity of the violation). Thank you and have a great time roleplaying! <br>
<br>
******************************************************<br>
<br>
